## Installation

```bash
# core (tree printer only)
pip install mydir

# PDF export (adds WeasyPrint)
pip install "mydir[pdf]"

# DOCX export
pip install "mydir[doc]"

# everything
pip install "mydir[pdf,doc]"
````

> **Windows**: WeasyPrint needs the GTKâ€‘Cairo runtime â€“ see the [official docs](https://weasyprint.org/docs/install/) for a oneâ€‘time setup.



## QuickÂ StartÂ â€”Â CLI

```bash
# Print current directory (folders first)
mydir tree .

# Include file sizes, files first, save to Markdown
mydir tree src --show-sizes --files-first -o tree.md

# Bundle the whole repo into a PDF (A4, 300â€¯DPI, 80â€¯% zoom)
mydir bundle . --pdf project.pdf --pdf-dpi 300 --pdf-scale 0.8
```

Run `mydir tree --help` or `mydir bundle --help` for all flags.



## QuickÂ StartÂ â€”Â PythonÂ API

```python
from mydir import mydir

tree = (
    mydir(root="src")
    .ignore("*.log", "__pycache__")
    .max_depth(2)
    .show_sizes_on()
)

print(tree.build_tree_str())          # â†’ console
tree.save("tree.md")                  # â†’ Markdown codeâ€‘block
tree.export_code_pdf("code.pdf")      # â†’ highlighted PDF
```



## CodeÂ BundleÂ Export

| Format | Extra install                | Notes                                                              |
| ------ | ---------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| PDF    | `pip install "mydir[pdf]"` | WeasyPrint under the hood; supports `--pdf-scale`, DPI & page size |
| DOCX   | `pip install "mydir[doc]"` | Uses `pythonâ€‘docx`; retains syntax colours via inline styles       |

Both exports walk the project, guess lexers with **Pygments**, and embed fileâ€‘path headings for easy navigation.



## AdvancedÂ Usage

```bash
# Reverse alphabetical, ignore build artefacts
mydir tree . --reverse --ignore dist build "*.egg-info"

# Generate JSON (parseable) via Python
from json import loads
json_lines = loads(mydir(root=".").to_json())
```



